cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on a wireless powered mobile edge computing system and studies the cooperation between wireless users, which involves communication and networking aspects. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes an optimization problem to maximize the amount of data that can be processed within a given time frame, which involves information theory and communication theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the joint optimization of system parameters such as transmit power and CPU frequency, which involves control theory and system optimization. 
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper studies the offloading of computation tasks to an edge server, which involves distributed computing and parallel computing. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the potential application of the proposed method in multimedia processing, which involves multimedia computing and processing.
